# Code Cleanup & Standards

## Code Cleanup Checklist

Run through this checklist when asked to do a "code cleanup" or "code cleanup for staged changes":

- Delete unused imports, variables, functions, and components
- Check ESLint compliance
- Verify Prettier/formatting consistency

## Code Standards

- Re-use existing components; create shared/common components for repeated UI patterns
- Maintain consistency in code structure and naming conventions
- Keep code clean, readable, and no more complex than necessary
- Prefer CSS classes (index.css) over inline styles; use inline only for dynamic values (e.g. gradients)
- Follow the existing component structure and folder organization
- Ensure proper error handling and validation where applicable
- Remove unused imports, variables, and console logs before finishing any task
